=====================================================================

000 Bounding box calculation is _very_ lousy when there are rotations
    in the scenegraph (ouch!). To reproduce in a way that shows off
    the bug well, load this scenegraph into the
    SoGuiExamples/engines/computebbox example:

    ---8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<----
    #Inventor V2.0 ascii
    
    Separator {
       Cube { }
       Rotation { rotation 0 0 1  0.785389 }
       Cube { }
    }
    ---8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<----

    This bug has very nasty implications for some types of models, as
    the bbox calculation error tend to accumulate -- so one can
    quickly end up with some horribly bad fitting bboxes.

    Bug reported by Nigel Murry. Write-down by <mortene@sim.no>,
    20020204.

=====================================================================

001 Writing draggers to file dumps the full set of parts. Reproduce
    with this minimal example:

    ---8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<----
    #include <Inventor/SoInteraction.h>
    #include <Inventor/draggers/SoTranslate1Dragger.h>
    #include <Inventor/actions/SoWriteAction.h>
    
    int
    main(void)
    {
      SoInteraction::init();
    
      SoTranslate1Dragger * dragger = new SoTranslate1Dragger;
      dragger->ref();
    
      SoWriteAction wa;
      wa.apply(dragger);
    
      dragger->unref();
      return 0;
    }
    ---8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<----

    <mortene@sim.no> 20020205.

=====================================================================

002 Trying to parse this file causes an assert failure / crash (which
    should _never_ happen, of course, no matter how wrong the file
    is):

    ---8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<----
    #Inventor V2.1 ascii
    
    Separator {
       TransformerDragger {
          translator1Switch Switch { }
          translator1LocateGroup LocateHighlight { }
       }
    }
    ---8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<-------8<----

    => /home/mortene/code/coin-head/src/nodekits/SoBaseKit.cpp:1686:
         SbBool SoBaseKit::setPart(int, SoNode *):
         Assertion `oldIdx >= 0' failed.

    (After this has been fixed, should also try to fully export the
    internals of an unmodified SoTransformerDragger and then read it
    back in again, as the file above is a _very_ cut-down version of
    such a dump.)

    <mortene@sim.no> 20020205.

